description: Fortune Bay Corp. acquires, explores for, and develops mineral properties. It primarily explores for gold deposits. The company holds a 100% interest in the Goldfields project comprises 12 mineral dispositions covering an area of approximately 5,000 hectares located in northern Saskatchewan, Canada; the Strike Uranium project that comprises four mineral dispositions covering an area of approximately 10,000 hectares located near Uranium City, northern Saskatchewan, Canada; the Murmac Uranium project, which consists of 10 mineral claims covering an area of approximately 5,300 hectares located in northern Saskatchewan, Canada; and the Ixhuat√°n project that consists of the 4,176 hectares of Rio Negro concession located in northern Chiapas State, Mexico. It also owns 2% net smelter royalty in the Huizopa project located in the Sierra Madres in Chihuahua, Mexico. The company is headquartered in Halifax, Canada.
